===Interjection===
'''eh'''
#('''eh?''') Used as a [[tag question]], to emphasise what goes before or to request that the listener confirm or agree with what has been said.
<!--other definitions?-->
#:''These hot dogs are pretty good, eh?''
#used to mean "[[What]]?"

====Usage notes====
This term is stereotypically associated with [[Canada]]. Some uses of it outside of [[Canada]] can convey that you are trying to sound (sarcastically) Canadian. However, it is in wide use in many other parts of the world, including the northern United States, Australia, New Zealand, and South Africa.

